parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death to occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the "Service Air Bag" message displays
the passenger airbag sensor is faulty
and the airbag system fails to recognize occupants in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to increased stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake system fails to function properly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and the brake fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can lead to engine stalling, loss of power, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The fuel level indicator is inaccurate
the fuel level drops rapidly
and the fuel system leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key becomes stuck in the ignition
the vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving
the instrument panel gauges malfunction
the security system fails
and the airbag warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger airbag light stays on
and the airbag may deploy unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key becomes stuck in the ignition
the vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving
and the ignition switch fails to turn over.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge fails to read the fuel level
and the vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving.
